# Description
This site integrates AI-generated content and maintains context for LLM interactions. The `llms.txt` file in the public directory provides context for AI assistants working on the project, and AI-generated features like summaries and callouts should follow established patterns.

# Guidelines
- **LLM Context File**: Maintain `/public/llms.txt` as the authoritative source of project context for AI assistants
- **AI-Generated Summaries**: When adding AI-generated post summaries, store them in DatoCMS, not as local files
- **Content Enhancement**: Use AI for content enhancement (meta descriptions, social share text) but store results in DatoCMS
- **Code Generation**: AI-generated code should follow existing patterns in the codebase
- **Documentation**: AI-generated documentation should be validated against actual implementation
- **Static Assets**: Place AI context files and resources in `/public/` directory for universal access

# Examples

## LLM Context File Structure
```text
# Project: ElPuas.com - Astro + DatoCMS Blog
## Architecture
- Astro static site generator
- DatoCMS headless CMS
- All content via GraphQL API
- No local markdown files

## Key Patterns
[Technical documentation for AI context]
```

## AI-Enhanced Meta Tags
```javascript
// When generating meta descriptions, use DatoCMS SEO fields
const descriptionTag = seoMetaTags?.find(tag => 
    tag.attributes?.property === 'og:description'
);
const metaDescription = descriptionTag ? 
    descriptionTag.attributes.content : 
    'AI-generated fallback description';
```

## Social Share Integration
```astro
---
// AI can enhance social sharing text while respecting DatoCMS structure
const socialShareData = {
    title: metaTitle,
    description: metaDescription, // From DatoCMS or AI-enhanced
    url: Astro.url.href
};
---
<SocialShare
    buttons={BUTTONS}
    description={socialShareData.description}
    title={socialShareData.title}
/>
```

